HEADWORD: Stoichiometry
<hw>Stoi`chi*om"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a
first principle, or element + <ets>-metry</ets>.]</ety> <def>The art or
process of calculating the atomic proportions, combining weights, and
other numerical relations of chemical elements and their
compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

